<p>The <code>substr</code> function extracts a substring by position and length.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | substr(0, 5){close}</pre>
<p>First 5 chars: <b>{echo $sampleText | substr(0, 5)}</b></p>

<h2>From Position</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'Hello World' | substr(6){close}</pre>
<p>From position 6: <b>{echo 'Hello World' | substr(6)}</b></p>

<h2>Negative Index</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'Hello World' | substr(-5){close}</pre>
<p>Last 5 chars: <b>{echo 'Hello World' | substr(-5)}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | substr(0, 10) | upper{close}</pre>
<p>First 10 uppercase: <b>{echo $sampleText | substr(0, 10) | upper}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'abcdefghij' | substr(2, 4) | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Middle portion: <b>{echo 'abcdefghij' | substr(2, 4) | upper}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo $email | substr(0, 3) | upper{close}</pre>
<p>First 3 of email: <b>{echo $email | substr(0, 3) | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Parameters: <code>substr(start, length)</code>. Negative start counts from end.</p>
